{"1":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.1","c":"وَالنَّجْمِ","d":"wlٱَngَّjmِْ","e":"wal-najmi"},{"b":"2.2","h":"2.1","c":"إِذَا","d":"ʾidِhāَ","e":"idhā"},{"b":"2.9","h":"3.15","c":"هَوَى","d":"hwَàَٰ","e":"hawā"}],"a":{"g":"By the star when it descends,"}},"2":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.4","c":"مَا","d":"māَ","e":"mā"},{"b":"0.42","h":"0.92","c":"ضَلَّ","d":"ḍlََّ","e":"ḍalla"},{"b":"1.1","h":"1.88","c":"صَاحِبُكُمْ","d":"ṣāَḥbِkُmُْ","e":"ṣāḥibukum"},{"b":"2.5","h":"3.96","c":"وَمَا","d":"wmَāَ","e":"wamā"},{"b":"3.2","h":"5.07","c":"غَوَى","d":"غwَàَٰ","e":"ghawā"}],"a":{"g":"Your companion [Muhammad] has not strayed, nor has he erred,"}},"3":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.5","c":"وَمَا","d":"wmَāَ","e":"wamā"},{"b":"0.65","h":"1.4","c":"يَنْطِقُ","d":"ynَṭqُِ","e":"yanṭiqu"},{"b":"2.4","h":"3.04","c":"عَنِ","d":"عʿnَِ","e":"ʿani"},{"b":"2.9","h":"3.75","c":"الْهَوَى","d":"lٱhْwَàَٰٓ","e":"l-hawā"}],"a":{"g":"Nor does he speak from [his own] inclination."}},"4":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.15","c":"إِنْ","d":"ʾinِْ","e":"in"},{"b":"0.43","h":"0.61","c":"هُوَ","d":"hwَُ","e":"huwa"},{"b":"0.87","h":"1.24","c":"إِلَّا","d":"ʾilِāَّ","e":"illā"},{"b":"1.7","h":"2.52","c":"وَحْيٌ","d":"wḥَàٌْ","e":"waḥyun"},{"b":"3.2","h":"3.53","c":"يُوحَى","d":"ywُḥàَٰ","e":"yūḥā"}],"a":{"g":"It is not but a revelation revealed,"}},"5":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.4","c":"عَلَّمَهُ","d":"عʿlَmَّhَۥُ","e":"ʿallamahu"},{"b":"1.3","h":"2.19","c":"شَدِيدُ","d":"shdَyِdُ","e":"shadīdu"},{"b":"2.2","h":"3.62","c":"الْقُوَى","d":"lٱqْwُàَٰ","e":"l-quwā"}],"a":{"g":"Taught to him by one intense in strength -","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                وهو المراد بقوله تعالى علمه شديد القوى ذو مرة فاستوى وهو بالافق الأعلى إلى آخر هذه الآيات وفي مثل هذه الأحوال من الصفاء يقع الاطلاع على ضمائر القلوب وقد يعبر عن ذلك الاطلاع بالتفرس ولذلك قال صلى الله عليه وسلم اتقوا فراسة المؤمن فإنه ينظر بنور الله حديث اتقوا فراسة المؤمن فإنه ينظر بنور الله تعالى أخرجه الترمذي من حديث أبي سعيد وقال حديث غريب وقد حكى أن رجلا من المجوس كان يدور على المسلمين ويقول ما معنى قول النبي صلى الله عليه وسلم اتقوا فراسة المؤمن فكان يذكر له تفسيره فلا يقنعه ذلك حتى انتهى إلى بعض المشايخ من الصوفية فسأله فقال له معناه أن تقطع الزنار الذي على وسطك تحت ثوبك فقال صدقت هذا معناه وأسلم وقال الآن عرفت أنك مؤمن\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, this is what is intended by His, the Exalted's, saying: \"Taught to him by one of intense power [shadid al-quwa], endowed with soundness [dhu mirrah], and he rose [fa-stawa] to his true form at the highest horizon [al-ufuq al-a'la]\" to the end of these verses. And in such states of purity [safa'] occurs the unveiling [al-ittila'] of the innermost secrets [dama'ir] of the hearts [qulub]. And that unveiling [al-ittila'] is sometimes expressed as 'discernment' [al-tafarruṣ]. And for that reason, the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said: \"Be mindful of the discernment [firasah] of the believer, for he sees by the light [nur] of God.\" The hadith \"Be mindful of the discernment [firasah] of the believer, for he sees by the light [nur] of God, the Exalted\" was reported by al-Tirmidhi from the narration of Abu Sa'id, and he said it is a rare [gharib] hadith. And it has been narrated that a man from the Magians [al-Majus] would go around among the Muslims saying, \"What is the meaning of the saying of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, 'Be mindful of the discernment [firasah] of the believer'?\" And its interpretation [tafsir] would be mentioned to him, but that would not satisfy him, until he came to one of the shaykhs from the Sufis [al-Sufiyyah] and asked him. So he said to him, \"Its meaning is that you cut the girdle [al-zunnar] which is around your waist beneath your garment.\" So he said, \"You have spoken the truth. This is its meaning,\" and he embraced Islam, and said, \"Now I have known that you are a believer.\"\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"6":{"w":[{"b":"0.04","h":"0.25","c":"ذُو","d":"dhwُ","e":"dhū"},{"b":"0.54","h":"0.98","c":"مِرَّةٍ","d":"mrِẗٍَّ","e":"mirratin"},{"b":"2.4","h":"3.12","c":"فَاسْتَوَى","d":"fsٱَtْwَàَٰ","e":"fa-is'tawā"}],"a":{"g":"One of soundness. And he rose to [his] true form"}},"7":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.23","c":"وَهُوَ","d":"whَwَُ","e":"wahuwa"},{"b":"0.68","h":"1.16","c":"بِالْأُفُقِ","d":"blٱِʾْafُqُِ","e":"bil-ufuqi"},{"b":"1.8","h":"2.84","c":"الْأَعْلَى","d":"lٱʾْaعَʿlْàَٰ","e":"l-aʿlā"}],"a":{"g":"While he was in the higher [part of the] horizon."}},"8":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.8","c":"ثُمَّ","d":"thmَُّ","e":"thumma"},{"b":"1.2","h":"2.11","c":"دَنَا","d":"dnَāَ","e":"danā"},{"b":"1.9","h":"3.09","c":"فَتَدَلَّى","d":"ftَdَlَàَّٰ","e":"fatadallā"}],"a":{"g":"Then he approached and descended"}},"9":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.35","c":"فَكَانَ","d":"fkَāَnَ","e":"fakāna"},{"b":"0.9","h":"1.56","c":"قَابَ","d":"qāَbَ","e":"qāba"},{"b":"1.5","h":"2.64","c":"قَوْسَيْنِ","d":"qwَsْyَnِْ","e":"qawsayni"},{"b":"2.8","h":"4.4","c":"أَوْ","d":"ʾawَْ","e":"aw"},{"b":"3.2","h":"5.1","c":"أَدْنَى","d":"ʾadَnْàَٰ","e":"adnā"}],"a":{"g":"And was at a distance of two bow lengths or nearer."}},"10":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.8","c":"فَأَوْحَى","d":"fʾَawَḥْàَٰٓ","e":"fa-awḥā"},{"b":"2.4","h":"3.39","c":"إِلَى","d":"ʾilِàَٰ","e":"ilā"},{"b":"3.0","h":"4.29","c":"عَبْدِهِ","d":"عʿbَdْhِۦِ","e":"ʿabdihi"},{"b":"4.3","h":"6.16","c":"مَا","d":"māَٓ","e":"mā"},{"b":"5.9","h":"6.26","c":"أَوْحَى","d":"ʾawَḥْàَٰ","e":"awḥā"}],"a":{"g":"And he revealed to His Servant what he revealed."}},"11":{"w":[{"b":"0.06","h":"0.35","c":"مَا","d":"māَ","e":"mā"},{"b":"0.47","h":"0.98","c":"كَذَبَ","d":"kdَhbََ","e":"kadhaba"},{"b":"1.1","h":"2.02","c":"الْفُؤَادُ","d":"lٱfْʾُwāَdُ","e":"l-fuādu"},{"b":"2.3","h":"3.88","c":"مَا","d":"māَ","e":"mā"},{"b":"2.7","h":"4.64","c":"رَأَى","d":"rʾَaàَٰٓ","e":"raā"}],"a":{"g":"The heart did not lie [about] what it saw.","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                ولموازنة البصيرة الباطنة للبصر الظاهر سماه الله تعالى باسمه فقال ما كذب الفؤاد ما رأى سمى إدراك الفؤاد رؤية\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, to equate the inner insight [al-basirah al-batinah] with the outer sight [al-basr al-zahir], Allah the Exalted named it with His name, saying: \"The heart [al-fu'ad] did not lie about what it saw [ma ra'a].\" He named the perception [idrak] of the heart [al-fu'ad] a seeing [ru'yah].\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"12":{"w":[{"b":"0.07","h":"0.6","c":"أَفَتُمَارُونَهُ","d":"ʾafَtَmُrَٰwُnhَۥُ","e":"afatumārūnahu"},{"b":"2.2","h":"3.78","c":"عَلَى","d":"عʿlَàَٰ","e":"ʿalā"},{"b":"3.0","h":"4.9","c":"مَا","d":"māَ","e":"mā"},{"b":"3.5","h":"5.77","c":"يَرَى","d":"yrَàَٰ","e":"yarā"}],"a":{"g":"So will you dispute with him over what he saw?"}},"13":{"w":[{"b":"0.04","h":"0.3","c":"وَلَقَدْ","d":"wlَqَdَْ","e":"walaqad"},{"b":"0.83","h":"1.28","c":"رَءَاهُ","d":"rءَāَhُ","e":"raāhu"},{"b":"1.8","h":"2.8","c":"نَزْلَةً","d":"nzَlْẗًَ","e":"nazlatan"},{"b":"2.9","h":"4.58","c":"أُخْرَى","d":"ʾakُhrْàَٰ","e":"ukh'rā"}],"a":{"g":"And he certainly saw him in another descent"}},"14":{"w":[{"b":"0.08","h":"0.35","c":"عِنْدَ","d":"عʿnِdَ","e":"ʿinda"},{"b":"1.3","h":"1.53","c":"سِدْرَةِ","d":"sdِrْẗَِ","e":"sid'rati"},{"b":"2.3","h":"2.87","c":"الْمُنْتَهَى","d":"lٱmْnُthَàَٰ","e":"l-muntahā"}],"a":{"g":"At the Lote Tree of the Utmost Boundary -"}},"15":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.55","c":"عِنْدَهَا","d":"عʿnِdhَāَ","e":"ʿindahā"},{"b":"1.9","h":"2.66","c":"جَنَّةُ","d":"gjnَẗَُّ","e":"jannatu"},{"b":"3.6","h":"4.41","c":"الْمَأْوَى","d":"lٱmْʾَawْàَٰٓ","e":"l-mawā"}],"a":{"g":"Near it is the Garden of Refuge -"}},"16":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.8","c":"إِذْ","d":"ʾidِhْ","e":"idh"},{"b":"0.39","h":"1.31","c":"يَغْشَى","d":"yغَsْhàَ","e":"yaghshā"},{"b":"1.0","h":"2.32","c":"السِّدْرَةَ","d":"lٱsdِّrْẗََ","e":"l-sid'rata"},{"b":"2.2","h":"3.99","c":"مَا","d":"māَ","e":"mā"},{"b":"2.7","h":"4.8","c":"يَغْشَى","d":"yغَsْhàَٰ","e":"yaghshā"}],"a":{"g":"When there covered the Lote Tree that which covered [it]."}},"17":{"w":[{"b":"0.05","h":"0.4","c":"مَا","d":"māَ","e":"mā"},{"b":"0.47","h":"0.96","c":"زَاغَ","d":"zāَغَ","e":"zāgha"},{"b":"1.2","h":"2.14","c":"الْبَصَرُ","d":"lٱbْṣَrَُ","e":"l-baṣaru"},{"b":"2.2","h":"3.59","c":"وَمَا","d":"wmَāَ","e":"wamā"},{"b":"2.8","h":"4.6","c":"طَغَى","d":"ṭغَàَٰ","e":"ṭaghā"}],"a":{"g":"The sight [of the Prophet] did not swerve, nor did it transgress [its limit]."}},"18":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.15","c":"لَقَدْ","d":"lqَdَْ","e":"laqad"},{"b":"0.62","h":"0.86","c":"رَأَى","d":"rʾَaàَٰ","e":"raā"},{"b":"1.3","h":"2.06","c":"مِنْ","d":"mnِْ","e":"min"},{"b":"1.8","h":"2.79","c":"ءَايَاتِ","d":"ءāَytَِٰ","e":"āyāti"},{"b":"2.9","h":"4.66","c":"رَبِّهِ","d":"rbَhِِّ","e":"rabbihi"},{"b":"3.9","h":"6.16","c":"الْكُبْرَى","d":"lٱkْbُrْàَٰٓ","e":"l-kub'rā"}],"a":{"g":"He certainly saw of the greatest signs of his Lord."}},"19":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.8","c":"أَفَرَءَيْتُمُ","d":"ʾafَrَءَyَtْmُُ","e":"afara-aytumu"},{"b":"1.6","h":"2.85","c":"اللَّاتَ","d":"lٱltََّٰ","e":"l-lāta"},{"b":"2.6","h":"4.26","c":"وَالْعُزَّى","d":"wlٱَعْʿzُàَّٰ","e":"wal-ʿuzā"}],"a":{"g":"So have you considered al-Lat and al-'Uzza?"}},"20":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.2","c":"وَمَنَوةَ","d":"wmَnَwَẗَٰ","e":"wamanata"},{"b":"1.1","h":"1.73","c":"الثَّالِثَةَ","d":"lٱthāَّltِhẗََ","e":"l-thālithata"},{"b":"2.5","h":"3.8","c":"الْأُخْرَى","d":"lٱʾْakُhrْàَٰٓ","e":"l-ukh'rā"}],"a":{"g":"And Manat, the third - the other one?"}},"21":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.5","c":"أَلَكُمُ","d":"ʾalَkَmُُ","e":"alakumu"},{"b":"0.88","h":"2.09","c":"الذَّكَرُ","d":"lٱdhkَّrَُ","e":"l-dhakaru"},{"b":"1.8","h":"3.13","c":"وَلَهُ","d":"wlَhَُ","e":"walahu"},{"b":"2.5","h":"4.14","c":"الْأُنْثَى","d":"lٱʾْanُthàَٰ","e":"l-unthā"}],"a":{"g":"Is the male for you and for Him the female?"}},"22":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.5","c":"تِلْكَ","d":"tlِkَْ","e":"til'ka"},{"b":"0.62","h":"1.3","c":"إِذًا","d":"ʾidِhāً","e":"idhan"},{"b":"1.0","h":"2.61","c":"قِسْمَةٌ","d":"qsِmْẗٌَ","e":"qis'matun"},{"b":"4.4","h":"4.89","c":"ضِيزَى","d":"ḍyِzàَٰٓ","e":"ḍīzā"}],"a":{"g":"That, then, is an unjust division."}},"23":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.03","c":"إِنْ","d":"ʾinِْ","e":"in"},{"b":"0.44","h":"0.69","c":"هِيَ","d":"hàَِ","e":"hiya"},{"b":"0.89","h":"1.38","c":"إِلَّا","d":"ʾilِāَّٓ","e":"illā"},{"b":"2.8","h":"3.66","c":"أَسْمَاءٌ","d":"ʾasَmْāَءٌٓ","e":"asmāon"},{"b":"6.4","h":"7.04","c":"سَمَّيْتُمُوهَا","d":"smَyَّtْmُwُhāَٓ","e":"sammaytumūhā"},{"b":"13.0","h":"10.02","c":"أَنْتُمْ","d":"ʾanَtmُْ","e":"antum"},{"b":"15.8","h":"13.54","c":"وَءَابَاؤُكُمْ","d":"wءَāَbāَʾٓwkُmُ","e":"waābāukum"},{"b":"19.8","h":"17.38","c":"مَا","d":"māَّٓ","e":"mā"},{"b":"19.8","h":"17.76","c":"أَنْزَلَ","d":"ʾanَzlََ","e":"anzala"},{"b":"22.8","h":"20.88","c":"اللَّهُ","d":"lٱlhَُّ","e":"l-lahu"},{"b":"23.8","h":"22.36","c":"بِهَا","d":"bhِāَ","e":"bihā"},{"b":"24.5","h":"23.42","c":"مِنْ","d":"mnِ","e":"min"},{"b":"25.7","h":"24.5","c":"سُلْطَانٍ","d":"slُṭْnٍَٰ","e":"sul'ṭānin"},{"b":"29.","h":"31.4","c":"إِنْ","d":"ʾinِ","e":"in"},{"b":"30.3","h":"32.42","c":"يَتَّبِعُونَ","d":"ytَbَّعِʿwُnَ","e":"yattabiʿūna"},{"b":"31.","h":"34.68","c":"إِلَّا","d":"ʾilِāَّ","e":"illā"},{"b":"32.5","h":"35.6","c":"الظَّنَّ","d":"lٱẓnََّّ","e":"l-ẓana"},{"b":"34.1","h":"37.44","c":"وَمَا","d":"wmَāَ","e":"wamā"},{"b":"34.7","h":"38.48","c":"تَهْوَى","d":"thَwْàَ","e":"tahwā"},{"b":"35.5","h":"39.61","c":"الْأَنْفُسُ","d":"lٱʾْanَfsُُ","e":"l-anfusu"},{"b":"38.3","h":"43.25","c":"وَلَقَدْ","d":"wlَqَdَْ","e":"walaqad"},{"b":"39.1","h":"44.49","c":"جَاءَهُمْ","d":"gjāَءٓhَmُ","e":"jāahum"},{"b":"42.9","h":"47.68","c":"مِنْ","d":"mnِّ","e":"min"},{"b":"43.1","h":"47.87","c":"رَبِّهِمُ","d":"rbَّhِّmُِ","e":"rabbihimu"},{"b":"44.5","h":"50.2","c":"الْهُدَى","d":"lٱhْdُàَٰٓ","e":"l-hudā"}],"a":{"g":"They are not but [mere] names you have named them - you and your forefathers - for which Allah has sent down no authority. They follow not except assumption and what [their] souls desire, and there has already come to them from their Lord guidance."}},"24":{"w":[{"b":"0.04","h":"0.55","c":"أَمْ","d":"ʾamَْ","e":"am"},{"b":"0.4","h":"1.1","c":"لِلْإِنْسَانِ","d":"llِʾْinِsnَِٰ","e":"lil'insāni"},{"b":"2.8","h":"4.02","c":"مَا","d":"māَ","e":"mā"},{"b":"3.2","h":"4.72","c":"تَمَنَّى","d":"tmَnَàَّٰ","e":"tamannā"}],"a":{"g":"Or is there for man whatever he wishes?"}},"25":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.35","c":"فَلِلَّهِ","d":"flَlِhَِّ","e":"falillahi"},{"b":"1.3","h":"2.22","c":"الْءَاخِرَةُ","d":"lٱءْāَkhrِẗَُ","e":"l-ākhiratu"},{"b":"2.6","h":"4.32","c":"وَالْأُولَى","d":"wlٱَʾْawُlàَٰ","e":"wal-ūlā"}],"a":{"g":"Rather, to Allah belongs the Hereafter and the first [life]."}},"26":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.79","c":"وَكَمْ","d":"wkَmَ","e":"wakam"},{"b":"1.3","h":"2.57","c":"مِنْ","d":"mnِّ","e":"min"},{"b":"2.5","h":"3.69","c":"مَلَكٍ","d":"mlَّkٍَ","e":"malakin"},{"b":"3.9","h":"5.37","c":"فِي","d":"fàِ","e":"fī"},{"b":"4.2","h":"5.74","c":"السَّمَاوَاتِ","d":"lٱsmَّwَٰtَِٰ","e":"l-samāwāti"},{"b":"5.9","h":"8.2","c":"لَا","d":"lāَ","e":"lā"},{"b":"6.2","h":"8.8","c":"تُغْنِي","d":"tغُnْàِ","e":"tugh'nī"},{"b":"7.1","h":"10.12","c":"شَفَاعَتُهُمْ","d":"shfَعَٰʿtَhُmُْ","e":"shafāʿatuhum"},{"b":"8.8","h":"12.74","c":"شَيْئًا","d":"shyَـْāًٔ","e":"shayan"},{"b":"14.","h":"13.25","c":"إِلَّا","d":"ʾilِāَّ","e":"illā"},{"b":"15.2","h":"13.89","c":"مِنْ","d":"mnِۢ","e":"min"},{"b":"16.5","h":"16.75","c":"بَعْدِ","d":"bعَʿdِْ","e":"baʿdi"},{"b":"17.2","h":"17.91","c":"أَنْ","d":"ʾanَ","e":"an"},{"b":"18.2","h":"19.03","c":"يَأْذَنَ","d":"yʾَadْhnََ","e":"yadhana"},{"b":"19.0","h":"20.29","c":"اللَّهُ","d":"lٱlhَُّ","e":"l-lahu"},{"b":"20.0","h":"21.76","c":"لِمَنْ","d":"lmِnَ","e":"liman"},{"b":"21.1","h":"23.3","c":"يَشَاءُ","d":"ysَhāَءُٓ","e":"yashāu"},{"b":"23.4","h":"25.71","c":"وَيَرْضَى","d":"wyَrَḍْàَٰٓ","e":"wayarḍā"}],"a":{"g":"And how many angels there are in the heavens whose intercession will not avail at all except [only] after Allah has permitted [it] to whom He wills and approves."}},"27":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.9","c":"إِنَّ","d":"ʾinَِّ","e":"inna"},{"b":"1.7","h":"2.17","c":"الَّذِينَ","d":"lٱdَّhyِnَ","e":"alladhīna"},{"b":"2.9","h":"3.89","c":"لَا","d":"lāَ","e":"lā"},{"b":"3.3","h":"4.57","c":"يُؤْمِنُونَ","d":"yʾُwmْnِwُnَ","e":"yu'minūna"},{"b":"4.7","h":"6.54","c":"بِالْءَاخِرَةِ","d":"blٱِءْāَkhrِẗَِ","e":"bil-ākhirati"},{"b":"6.3","h":"8.91","c":"لَيُسَمُّونَ","d":"lyَsُmَwُّnَ","e":"layusammūna"},{"b":"8.7","h":"11.57","c":"الْمَلَائِكَةَ","d":"lٱmْlَʾَٰٓykِẗََ","e":"l-malāikata"},{"b":"11.8","h":"14.73","c":"تَسْمِيَةَ","d":"tsَmْyِẗََ","e":"tasmiyata"},{"b":"12.9","h":"16.61","c":"الْأُنْثَى","d":"lٱʾْanُthàَٰ","e":"l-unthā"}],"a":{"g":"Indeed, those who do not believe in the Hereafter name the angels female names,"}},"28":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.87","c":"وَمَا","d":"wmَāَ","e":"wamā"},{"b":"0.66","h":"1.83","c":"لَهُمْ","d":"lhَmُ","e":"lahum"},{"b":"2.1","h":"3.19","c":"بِهِ","d":"bhِۦِ","e":"bihi"},{"b":"2.9","h":"4.28","c":"مِنْ","d":"mnِْ","e":"min"},{"b":"3.3","h":"4.84","c":"عِلْمٍ","d":"عʿlِmٍْ","e":"ʿil'min"},{"b":"4.4","h":"6.34","c":"إِنْ","d":"ʾinِ","e":"in"},{"b":"5.8","h":"7.39","c":"يَتَّبِعُونَ","d":"ytَbَّعِʿwُnَ","e":"yattabiʿūna"},{"b":"7.2","h":"9.69","c":"إِلَّا","d":"ʾilِāَّ","e":"illā"},{"b":"7.8","h":"10.74","c":"الظَّنَّ","d":"lٱẓnََّّ","e":"l-ẓana"},{"b":"9.5","h":"13.85","c":"وَإِنَّ","d":"wʾَinَِّ","e":"wa-inna"},{"b":"10.9","h":"15.49","c":"الظَّنَّ","d":"lٱẓnََّّ","e":"l-ẓana"},{"b":"12.3","h":"17.32","c":"لَا","d":"lāَ","e":"lā"},{"b":"12.7","h":"17.98","c":"يُغْنِي","d":"yغُnْàِ","e":"yugh'nī"},{"b":"13.7","h":"19.49","c":"مِنَ","d":"mnَِ","e":"mina"},{"b":"14.1","h":"20.05","c":"الْحَقِّ","d":"lٱḥْqَِّ","e":"l-ḥaqi"},{"b":"15.0","h":"21.43","c":"شَيْئًا","d":"shyَـْāًٔ","e":"shayan"}],"a":{"g":"And they have thereof no knowledge. They follow not except assumption, and indeed, assumption avails not against the truth at all."}},"29":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.75","c":"فَأَعْرِضْ","d":"fʾَaعَʿrْḍِْ","e":"fa-aʿriḍ"},{"b":"1.0","h":"2.17","c":"عَنْ","d":"عʿnَ","e":"ʿan"},{"b":"2.0","h":"3.39","c":"مَنْ","d":"mnَّ","e":"man"},{"b":"2.8","h":"4.37","c":"تَوَلَّى","d":"twَlَàَّٰ","e":"tawallā"},{"b":"3.9","h":"6.33","c":"عَنْ","d":"عʿnَ","e":"ʿan"},{"b":"5.0","h":"7.44","c":"ذِكْرِنَا","d":"dhkِrْnِāَ","e":"dhik'rinā"},{"b":"6.1","h":"9.25","c":"وَلَمْ","d":"wlَmَْ","e":"walam"},{"b":"6.8","h":"10.1","c":"يُرِدْ","d":"yrُdِْ","e":"yurid"},{"b":"7.5","h":"11.19","c":"إِلَّا","d":"ʾilِāَّ","e":"illā"},{"b":"8.1","h":"12.15","c":"الْحَيَوةَ","d":"lٱḥْyَwَẗَٰ","e":"l-ḥayata"},{"b":"9.3","h":"14","c":"الدُّنْيَا","d":"lٱdnُّyْāَ","e":"l-dun'yā"}],"a":{"g":"So turn away from whoever turns his back on Our message and desires not except the worldly life.","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                ولما انكشف لأولياء الله تعالى أن العبد مهلك نفسه بأعماله واتباعه هوى نفسه إهلاك دود القز نفسه: رفضوا الدنيا بالكلية، حتى قال الحسن: رأيت سبعين بدرياً كانوا فيما أحل الله لهم أزهد منكم فيما حرم الله عليكم. وفي لفظ آخر: كانوا بالبلاء أشد قرحاً منكم بالخصب والرخاء لو رأيتموهم قلتم مجانين، ولو رأوا خياركم قالوا ما لهؤلاء من خلاق، ولو رأوا أشراركم قالوا ما يؤمن هؤلاء بيوم الحساب. وكان أحدهم يعرض لهم المال الحلال فلا يأخذه ويقول: أخاف أن يفسد على قلبي، فمن كان له قلب فهو لا محالة يخاف من فساده، والذين أمات حب الدنيا قلوبهم فقد أخبر الله عنهم إذ قال تعالى: \" فأعرض عمن تولى عن ذكرنا ولم يرد إلا الحياة الدنيا، ذلك مبلغهم من العلم\"، فأحال ذلك كله على الغفلة وعدم العلم.\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, when it was unveiled [inkashafa] for the friends [awliya'] of God, the Exalted, that the servant destroys his own soul [nafs] by his actions and his following of his soul's [nafs] desire [hawa]—like the silkworm destroying itself—they rejected the world [dunya] completely. So much so that Al-Hasan said: \"I saw seventy of the Companions of Badr; they were, in what God had made lawful for them, more abstinent than you are in what God has forbidden for you.\" And in another wording: \"They were in hardship more wounded than you are in ease and plenty. If you saw them, you would say, 'They are madmen,' and if they saw the best of you, they would say, 'These have no share [khalāq],' and if they saw the worst of you, they would say, 'These do not believe in the Day of Reckoning.'\" And one of them would be offered lawful wealth and would not take it, saying, \"I fear it will corrupt my heart [qalb].\" For whoever possesses a heart [qalb] inevitably fears its corruption. And those whose hearts [qulub] have been killed by the love of the world [dunya]—God has informed about them when He, the Exalted, said: \"So turn away from him who turns away from Our Remembrance and desires nothing but the life of this world [dunya]. That is the extent of their knowledge ['ilm].\" He attributed all of that to heedlessness [ghafla] and the absence of knowledge ['ilm].\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"30":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.8","c":"ذَلِكَ","d":"dhlَٰkَِ","e":"dhālika"},{"b":"0.89","h":"1.98","c":"مَبْلَغُهُمْ","d":"mbَlْغَhُmُ","e":"mablaghuhum"},{"b":"3.0","h":"4.33","c":"مِنَ","d":"mnَِّ","e":"mina"},{"b":"3.3","h":"5.22","c":"الْعِلْمِ","d":"lٱعْʿlِmِْ","e":"l-ʿil'mi"},{"b":"4.6","h":"7.95","c":"إِنَّ","d":"ʾinَِّ","e":"inna"},{"b":"5.7","h":"8.98","c":"رَبَّكَ","d":"rbَkََّ","e":"rabbaka"},{"b":"6.5","h":"10.42","c":"هُوَ","d":"hwَُ","e":"huwa"},{"b":"7.0","h":"11.13","c":"أَعْلَمُ","d":"ʾaعَʿlْmَُ","e":"aʿlamu"},{"b":"7.9","h":"12.58","c":"بِمَنْ","d":"bmِnَ","e":"biman"},{"b":"9.2","h":"14","c":"ضَلَّ","d":"ḍlََّ","e":"ḍalla"},{"b":"9.8","h":"14.8","c":"عَنْ","d":"عʿnَ","e":"ʿan"},{"b":"10.7","h":"15.9","c":"سَبِيلِهِ","d":"sbَyِlhِۦِ","e":"sabīlihi"},{"b":"12.1","h":"18.19","c":"وَهُوَ","d":"whَwَُ","e":"wahuwa"},{"b":"12.8","h":"19.15","c":"أَعْلَمُ","d":"ʾaعَʿlْmَُ","e":"aʿlamu"},{"b":"13.7","h":"20.59","c":"بِمَنِ","d":"bmِnَِ","e":"bimani"},{"b":"14.3","h":"21.57","c":"اهْتَدَى","d":"hٱtْdَàَٰ","e":"ih'tadā"}],"a":{"g":"That is their sum of knowledge. Indeed, your Lord is most knowing of who strays from His way, and He is most knowing of who is guided."}},"31":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.47","c":"وَلِلَّهِ","d":"wlَlِhَِّ","e":"walillahi"},{"b":"1.4","h":"2.18","c":"مَا","d":"māَ","e":"mā"},{"b":"1.7","h":"2.83","c":"فِي","d":"fàِ","e":"fī"},{"b":"2.0","h":"3.17","c":"السَّمَاوَاتِ","d":"lٱsmَّwَٰtَِٰ","e":"l-samāwāti"},{"b":"3.6","h":"5.58","c":"وَمَا","d":"wmَāَ","e":"wamā"},{"b":"4.3","h":"6.59","c":"فِي","d":"fàِ","e":"fī"},{"b":"4.6","h":"7.06","c":"الْأَرْضِ","d":"lٱʾْarَḍِْ","e":"l-arḍi"},{"b":"5.5","h":"10.05","c":"لِيَجْزِيَ","d":"lyِgَjzْàَِ","e":"liyajziya"},{"b":"6.7","h":"11.49","c":"الَّذِينَ","d":"lٱdَّhyِnَ","e":"alladhīna"},{"b":"7.8","h":"13.12","c":"أَسَاءُوا","d":"ʾasَـَٰٓwُٔā۟","e":"asāū"},{"b":"10.8","h":"15.69","c":"بِمَا","d":"bmِāَ","e":"bimā"},{"b":"11.4","h":"16.5","c":"عَمِلُوا","d":"عʿmَlِwُā۟","e":"ʿamilū"},{"b":"12.5","h":"18.1","c":"وَيَجْزِيَ","d":"wyَgَjzْàَِ","e":"wayajziya"},{"b":"13.5","h":"19.55","c":"الَّذِينَ","d":"lٱdَّhyِnَ","e":"alladhīna"},{"b":"14.7","h":"21.23","c":"أَحْسَنُوا","d":"ʾaḥَsْnَwُā۟","e":"aḥsanū"},{"b":"15.8","h":"22.92","c":"بِالْحُسْنَى","d":"blٱِḥْsُnْàَ","e":"bil-ḥus'nā"}],"a":{"g":"And to Allah belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth - that He may recompense those who do evil with [the penalty of] what they have done and recompense those who do good with the best [reward] -","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                هنالك تجزى كل نفس بما كسبت إن الله عز وجل يقول \"ليجزى الذي أساءوا بما عملوا ويجزى الذي أحسنوا بالحسنى\"\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, there, every soul [nafs] will be recompensed for what it has earned. Indeed, Allah, the Mighty and Majestic, says: \"That He may recompense those who did evil for what they did, and recompense those who did good with the best [al-husna].\"\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"32":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.75","c":"الَّذِينَ","d":"lٱdَّhyِnَ","e":"alladhīna"},{"b":"1.2","h":"2.47","c":"يَجْتَنِبُونَ","d":"ygَjtْnَbِwُnَ","e":"yajtanibūna"},{"b":"2.8","h":"4.77","c":"كَبَائِرَ","d":"kbَʾَٰٓyrَِ","e":"kabāira"},{"b":"5.5","h":"7.11","c":"الْإِثْمِ","d":"lٱʾْitِhmِْ","e":"l-ith'mi"},{"b":"6.4","h":"8.37","c":"وَالْفَوَاحِشَ","d":"wlٱَfْwَḥَٰsِhَ","e":"wal-fawāḥisha"},{"b":"8.0","h":"10.76","c":"إِلَّا","d":"ʾilِāَّ","e":"illā"},{"b":"8.7","h":"11.7","c":"اللَّمَمَ","d":"lٱlmَّmََ","e":"l-lamama"},{"b":"10.1","h":"16","c":"إِنَّ","d":"ʾinَِّ","e":"inna"},{"b":"11.4","h":"17.3","c":"رَبَّكَ","d":"rbَkََّ","e":"rabbaka"},{"b":"12.3","h":"18.7","c":"وَاسِعُ","d":"wsَٰعِʿُ","e":"wāsiʿu"},{"b":"13.2","h":"20.15","c":"الْمَغْفِرَةِ","d":"lٱmْغَfْrِẗَِ","e":"l-maghfirati"},{"b":"15.1","h":"24.15","c":"هُوَ","d":"hwَُ","e":"huwa"},{"b":"15.5","h":"24.66","c":"أَعْلَمُ","d":"ʾaعَʿlْmَُ","e":"aʿlamu"},{"b":"16.3","h":"25.94","c":"بِكُمْ","d":"bkِmُْ","e":"bikum"},{"b":"17.0","h":"26.9","c":"إِذْ","d":"ʾidِhْ","e":"idh"},{"b":"17.","h":"27.43","c":"أَنْشَأَكُمْ","d":"ʾanَshʾَakَmُ","e":"ansha-akum"},{"b":"20.0","h":"30.43","c":"مِنَ","d":"mnَِّ","e":"mina"},{"b":"20.3","h":"30.93","c":"الْأَرْضِ","d":"lٱʾْarَḍِْ","e":"l-arḍi"},{"b":"21.3","h":"32.23","c":"وَإِذْ","d":"wʾَidِhْ","e":"wa-idh"},{"b":"21.9","h":"33.13","c":"أَنْتُمْ","d":"ʾanَtmُْ","e":"antum"},{"b":"23.5","h":"35.13","c":"أَجِنَّةٌ","d":"ʾagَjnِẗٌَّ","e":"ajinnatun"},{"b":"25.9","h":"37.74","c":"فِي","d":"fàِ","e":"fī"},{"b":"26.4","h":"38.53","c":"بُطُونِ","d":"bṭُwُnِ","e":"buṭūni"},{"b":"27.4","h":"40.89","c":"أُمَّهَاتِكُمْ","d":"ʾamُhَّtَٰkِmُْ","e":"ummahātikum"},{"b":"30.5","h":"46.4","c":"فَلَا","d":"flَāَ","e":"falā"},{"b":"31.1","h":"47.22","c":"تُزَكُّوا","d":"tzُkَwُّāٓ۟","e":"tuzakkū"},{"b":"34.1","h":"50.09","c":"أَنْفُسَكُمْ","d":"ʾanَfsُkَmُْ","e":"anfusakum"},{"b":"36.","h":"54.5","c":"هُوَ","d":"hwَُ","e":"huwa"},{"b":"37.","h":"54.97","c":"أَعْلَمُ","d":"ʾaعَʿlْmَُ","e":"aʿlamu"},{"b":"37.9","h":"56.24","c":"بِمَنِ","d":"bmِnَِ","e":"bimani"},{"b":"38.6","h":"57.11","c":"اتَّقَى","d":"tٱqَّàَٰٓ","e":"ittaqā"}],"a":{"g":"Those who avoid the major sins and immoralities, only [committing] slight ones. Indeed, your Lord is vast in forgiveness. He was most knowing of you when He produced you from the earth and when you were fetuses in the wombs of your mothers. So do not claim yourselves to be pure; He is most knowing of who fears Him.","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                بيان ذم العجب وآفاته اعلم أن العجب مذموم في كتاب الله تعالى وسنة رسوله ﭬ. وقد قال تعالى: \"فلا تزكوا أنفسكم\" قال ابن جريج: معناه إذا عملت خيراً فلا تقل عملت. وقال زيد بن أسلم. لا تبروها، أي لا تعتقدوا أنها بارة وهو معنى العجب. وقد قال تعالى \"لا تبطلوا صدقاتكم بالمن والأذى\" والمن نتيجة استعظام الصدقة، واستعظام العمل هو العجب. فظهر بهذا أن العجب مذموم جداً.\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, the explanation of the censure of self-admiration [al-'ujb] and its destructive consequences. Know that self-admiration [al-'ujb] is censured in the Book of Allah, the Most High, and the Sunnah of His Messenger, peace be upon him. And He, the Most High, has said: \"So do not claim purity for yourselves [fa la tuzakku anfusakum].\" Ibn Jurayj said: Its meaning is, when you perform a good deed, do not say, 'I performed it.' And Zayd ibn Aslam said: Do not declare them righteous, meaning do not believe they are righteous, and this is the meaning of self-admiration [al-'ujb]. And He, the Most High, has said: \"Do not invalidate your charities with reminders of your generosity [al-mann] or injury.\" And the reminder of generosity [al-mann] is the result of magnifying the charity, and magnifying the deed is self-admiration [al-'ujb]. Thus, it becomes clear by this that self-admiration [al-'ujb] is most severely censured.\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"33":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.55","c":"أَفَرَءَيْتَ","d":"ʾafَrَءَyَtَْ","e":"afara-ayta"},{"b":"1.2","h":"2.25","c":"الَّذِي","d":"lٱdَّhàِ","e":"alladhī"},{"b":"2.1","h":"3.52","c":"تَوَلَّى","d":"twَlَàَّٰ","e":"tawallā"}],"a":{"g":"Have you seen the one who turned away"}},"34":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.35","c":"وَأَعْطَى","d":"wʾَaعَʿṭْàَٰ","e":"wa-aʿṭā"},{"b":"1.0","h":"1.9","c":"قَلِيلًا","d":"qlَyِlāً","e":"qalīlan"},{"b":"1.9","h":"3.34","c":"وَأَكْدَى","d":"wʾَakَdْàَٰٓ","e":"wa-akdā"}],"a":{"g":"And gave a little and [then] refrained?"}},"35":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.35","c":"أَعِنْدَهُ","d":"ʾaعَʿnِdhَۥُ","e":"aʿindahu"},{"b":"1.8","h":"2.47","c":"عِلْمُ","d":"عʿlِmُْ","e":"ʿil'mu"},{"b":"2.5","h":"3.52","c":"الْغَيْبِ","d":"lٱغْyَbِْ","e":"l-ghaybi"},{"b":"3.3","h":"4.92","c":"فَهُوَ","d":"fhَwَُ","e":"fahuwa"},{"b":"4.0","h":"6","c":"يَرَى","d":"yrَàَٰٓ","e":"yarā"}],"a":{"g":"Does he have knowledge of the unseen, so he sees?"}},"36":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"1.15","c":"أَمْ","d":"ʾamَْ","e":"am"},{"b":"0.38","h":"1.59","c":"لَمْ","d":"lmَْ","e":"lam"},{"b":"0.79","h":"2.16","c":"يُنَبَّأْ","d":"ynُbَʾَّaْ","e":"yunabba"},{"b":"1.7","h":"3.74","c":"بِمَا","d":"bmِāَ","e":"bimā"},{"b":"2.4","h":"4.79","c":"فِي","d":"fàِ","e":"fī"},{"b":"2.9","h":"5.53","c":"صُحُفِ","d":"ṣḥُfُِ","e":"ṣuḥufi"},{"b":"3.6","h":"6.61","c":"مُوسَى","d":"mwُsàَٰ","e":"mūsā"}],"a":{"g":"Or has he not been informed of what was in the scriptures of Moses","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                وقال زياد خلوا سبيله، هذا رجل قد لقن حجته.\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                And Ziyad said, \"Leave his way, for this is a man whose argument has been instilled [luqqina hujjatuhu].\"\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"37":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"1","c":"وَإِبْرَاهِيمَ","d":"wʾَibِrْhَٰyِmَ","e":"wa-ib'rāhīma"},{"b":"1.6","h":"3.42","c":"الَّذِي","d":"lٱdَّhàِ","e":"alladhī"},{"b":"2.5","h":"4.83","c":"وَفَّى","d":"wfَàَّٰٓ","e":"waffā"}],"a":{"g":"And [of] Abraham, who fulfilled [his obligations] -","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                وروي أنه لما قال جبريل لإبراهيم عليهما السلام وقد رمي إلى النار بالمنجنيق: ألك حاجة؟ قال: أما إليك فلا، وفاءً بقوله حسبي الله ونعم الوكيل، إذا قال ذلك حين أخذ ليرمى، فأنزل الله تعالى: \" وإبراهيم الذي وفى \".\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, it is narrated that when Gabriel [Jibril], peace be upon them both, said to Abraham [Ibrahim] as he was catapulted into the fire, \"Do you have any need?\" he replied, \"Not from you,\" fulfilling his statement, \"Sufficient for me is Allah [Allah], and He is the best Disposer of affairs [al-Wakil],\" which he had said when he was taken to be thrown. Then Allah, the Exalted, revealed: \"And [of] Abraham who fulfilled [wa-Ibrahim alladhi waffa].\"\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"38":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.65","c":"أَلَّا","d":"ʾalَāَّ","e":"allā"},{"b":"0.8","h":"1.84","c":"تَزِرُ","d":"tzَrُِ","e":"taziru"},{"b":"1.5","h":"2.97","c":"وَازِرَةٌ","d":"wāَzrِẗٌَ","e":"wāziratun"},{"b":"3.4","h":"5.35","c":"وِزْرَ","d":"wzِrَْ","e":"wiz'ra"},{"b":"4.1","h":"6.33","c":"أُخْرَى","d":"ʾakُhrْàَٰ","e":"ukh'rā"}],"a":{"g":"That no bearer of burdens will bear the burden of another"}},"39":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.85","c":"وَأَنْ","d":"wʾَanَ","e":"wa-an"},{"b":"0.33","h":"1.33","c":"لَيْسَ","d":"lyَّsَْ","e":"laysa"},{"b":"1.2","h":"2.74","c":"لِلْإِنْسَانِ","d":"llِʾْinِsnَِٰ","e":"lil'insāni"},{"b":"3.6","h":"5.64","c":"إِلَّا","d":"ʾilِāَّ","e":"illā"},{"b":"4.5","h":"7.03","c":"مَا","d":"māَ","e":"mā"},{"b":"4.8","h":"7.83","c":"سَعَى","d":"sعَʿàَٰ","e":"saʿā"}],"a":{"g":"And that there is not for man except that [good] for which he strives","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                وقال في أمر الآخرة وأن ليس للإنسان إلا ما سعى فقد تكفل لك بأمر الدنيا خاصة وصرفك عن السعى فيها فكذبته بأفعالك وأصبحت تتكالبين على طلبها تكالب المدهوش المستهتر ووكل أمر الآخرة إلى سعيك فأعرضت عنها إعراض المغرور المستحقر.\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, concerning the matter of the Hereafter [al-akhirah] and that for man there is only what he strives for, He has guaranteed for you the matter of the world [al-dunya] specifically and diverted you from striving in it. Yet you have belied Him with your actions, and you have become one who scrambles in pursuit of it, scrambling like one who is bewildered and heedless. And He has entrusted the matter of the Hereafter [al-akhirah] to your striving, yet you have turned away from it, turning away like one who is deluded and contemptuous.\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"40":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.85","c":"وَأَنَّ","d":"wʾَanََّ","e":"wa-anna"},{"b":"1.2","h":"2.28","c":"سَعْيَهُ","d":"sعَʿyْhَۥُ","e":"saʿyahu"},{"b":"2.4","h":"4.09","c":"سَوْفَ","d":"swَfَْ","e":"sawfa"},{"b":"3.0","h":"5.2","c":"يُرَى","d":"yrُàَٰ","e":"yurā"}],"a":{"g":"And that his effort is going to be seen -"}},"41":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.35","c":"ثُمَّ","d":"thmَُّ","e":"thumma"},{"b":"1.0","h":"1.61","c":"يُجْزَاهُ","d":"ygُjzْàَhُٰ","e":"yuj'zāhu"},{"b":"2.1","h":"3.3","c":"الْجَزَاءَ","d":"lٱgْjzَāَءَٓ","e":"l-jazāa"},{"b":"4.7","h":"5.87","c":"الْأَوْفَى","d":"lٱʾْawَfْàَٰ","e":"l-awfā"}],"a":{"g":"Then he will be recompensed for it with the fullest recompense"}},"42":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.61","c":"وَأَنَّ","d":"wʾَanََّ","e":"wa-anna"},{"b":"1.4","h":"2.02","c":"إِلَى","d":"ʾilِàَٰ","e":"ilā"},{"b":"2.1","h":"3.06","c":"رَبِّكَ","d":"rbَkَِّ","e":"rabbika"},{"b":"3.0","h":"4.68","c":"الْمُنْتَهَى","d":"lٱmْnُthَàَٰ","e":"l-muntahā"}],"a":{"g":"And that to your Lord is the finality"}},"43":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.5","c":"وَأَنَّهُ","d":"wʾَanَhَّۥُ","e":"wa-annahu"},{"b":"1.8","h":"2.64","c":"هُوَ","d":"hwَُ","e":"huwa"},{"b":"2.2","h":"3.33","c":"أَضْحَكَ","d":"ʾaḍَḥْkََ","e":"aḍḥaka"},{"b":"3.1","h":"4.82","c":"وَأَبْكَى","d":"wʾَabَkْàَٰ","e":"wa-abkā"}],"a":{"g":"And that it is He who makes [one] laugh and weep"}},"44":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.65","c":"وَأَنَّهُ","d":"wʾَanَhَّۥُ","e":"wa-annahu"},{"b":"1.9","h":"2.78","c":"هُوَ","d":"hwَُ","e":"huwa"},{"b":"2.2","h":"3.5","c":"أَمَاتَ","d":"ʾamَāَtَ","e":"amāta"},{"b":"3.2","h":"4.98","c":"وَأَحْيَا","d":"wʾَaḥَyْāَ","e":"wa-aḥyā"}],"a":{"g":"And that it is He who causes death and gives life"}},"45":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.6","c":"وَأَنَّهُ","d":"wʾَanَhَّۥُ","e":"wa-annahu"},{"b":"1.8","h":"2.82","c":"خَلَقَ","d":"khlَqََ","e":"khalaqa"},{"b":"2.5","h":"3.9","c":"الزَّوْجَيْنِ","d":"lٱzwَّgْjyَnِْ","e":"l-zawjayni"},{"b":"4.1","h":"6.26","c":"الذَّكَرَ","d":"lٱdhkَّrََ","e":"l-dhakara"},{"b":"4.8","h":"7.25","c":"وَالْأُنْثَى","d":"wlٱَʾْanُthàَٰ","e":"wal-unthā"}],"a":{"g":"And that He creates the two mates - the male and female -"}},"46":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.7","c":"مِنْ","d":"mnِ","e":"min"},{"b":"0.99","h":"1.82","c":"نُطْفَةٍ","d":"nṭُّfْẗٍَ","e":"nuṭ'fatin"},{"b":"1.9","h":"3.4","c":"إِذَا","d":"ʾidِhāَ","e":"idhā"},{"b":"2.6","h":"4.41","c":"تُمْنَى","d":"tmُnْàَٰ","e":"tum'nā"}],"a":{"g":"From a sperm-drop when it is emitted"}},"47":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.06","c":"وَأَنَّ","d":"wʾَanََّ","e":"wa-anna"},{"b":"1.2","h":"1.42","c":"عَلَيْهِ","d":"عʿlَyَhِْ","e":"ʿalayhi"},{"b":"2.3","h":"2.85","c":"النَّشْأَةَ","d":"lٱnsَّhʾْaẗََ","e":"l-nashata"},{"b":"4.0","h":"4.73","c":"الْأُخْرَى","d":"lٱʾْakُhrْàَٰ","e":"l-ukh'rā"}],"a":{"g":"And that [incumbent] upon Him is the next creation"}},"48":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"1.15","c":"وَأَنَّهُ","d":"wʾَanَhَّۥُ","e":"wa-annahu"},{"b":"2.1","h":"3.27","c":"هُوَ","d":"hwَُ","e":"huwa"},{"b":"2.5","h":"3.97","c":"أَغْنَى","d":"ʾaغَnْàَٰ","e":"aghnā"},{"b":"3.4","h":"5.41","c":"وَأَقْنَى","d":"wʾَaqَnْàَٰ","e":"wa-aqnā"}],"a":{"g":"And that it is He who enriches and suffices"}},"49":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.8","c":"وَأَنَّهُ","d":"wʾَanَhَّۥُ","e":"wa-annahu"},{"b":"1.7","h":"2.75","c":"هُوَ","d":"hwَُ","e":"huwa"},{"b":"2.1","h":"3.48","c":"رَبُّ","d":"rbَُّ","e":"rabbu"},{"b":"2.8","h":"4.55","c":"الشِّعْرَى","d":"lٱshعِّʿrْàَٰ","e":"l-shiʿ'rā"}],"a":{"g":"And that it is He who is the Lord of Sirius"}},"50":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.55","c":"وَأَنَّهُ","d":"wʾَanَhَّۥُٓ","e":"wa-annahu"},{"b":"2.9","h":"3.62","c":"أَهْلَكَ","d":"ʾahَlْkََ","e":"ahlaka"},{"b":"3.7","h":"4.87","c":"عَادًا","d":"عʿāَdāً","e":"ʿādan"},{"b":"4.5","h":"6.37","c":"الْأُولَى","d":"lٱʾْawُlàَٰ","e":"l-ūlā"}],"a":{"g":"And that He destroyed the first [people of] 'Aad"}},"51":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.85","c":"وَثَمُودَ","d":"wtَhmَwُdāَ۟","e":"wathamūdā"},{"b":"1.1","h":"2.46","c":"فَمَا","d":"fmَāَٓ","e":"famā"},{"b":"3.4","h":"4.64","c":"أَبْقَى","d":"ʾabَqْàَٰ","e":"abqā"}],"a":{"g":"And Thamud - and He did not spare [them] -"}},"52":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.69","c":"وَقَوْمَ","d":"wqَwَmَْ","e":"waqawma"},{"b":"0.85","h":"1.95","c":"نُوحٍ","d":"nwُḥٍ","e":"nūḥin"},{"b":"2.4","h":"4.14","c":"مِنْ","d":"mnِّ","e":"min"},{"b":"3.7","h":"5.23","c":"قَبْلُ","d":"qbَlُْ","e":"qablu"},{"b":"4.7","h":"7.8","c":"إِنَّهُمْ","d":"ʾinِhَّmُْ","e":"innahum"},{"b":"6.6","h":"9.69","c":"كَانُوا","d":"kāَnwُā۟","e":"kānū"},{"b":"7.5","h":"11.2","c":"هُمْ","d":"hmُْ","e":"hum"},{"b":"8.0","h":"11.95","c":"أَظْلَمَ","d":"ʾaẓَlْmََ","e":"aẓlama"},{"b":"8.9","h":"13.41","c":"وَأَطْغَى","d":"wʾَaṭَغْàَٰ","e":"wa-aṭghā"}],"a":{"g":"And the people of Noah before. Indeed, it was they who were [even] more unjust and oppressing."}},"53":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.9","c":"وَالْمُؤْتَفِكَةَ","d":"wlٱَmْʾُwtْfَkِẗََ","e":"wal-mu'tafikata"},{"b":"1.8","h":"3.54","c":"أَهْوَى","d":"ʾahَwْàَٰ","e":"ahwā"}],"a":{"g":"And the overturned towns He hurled down"}},"54":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.8","c":"فَغَشَّاهَا","d":"fغَsَhàَّhٰāَ","e":"faghashāhā"},{"b":"1.5","h":"3.31","c":"مَا","d":"māَ","e":"mā"},{"b":"1.9","h":"4.14","c":"غَشَّى","d":"غsَhàَّٰ","e":"ghashā"}],"a":{"g":"And covered them by that which He covered."}},"55":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.7","c":"فَبِأَيِّ","d":"fbَʾِaàَِّ","e":"fabi-ayyi"},{"b":"1.1","h":"2.3","c":"ءَالَاءِ","d":"ءāَlāَءِٓ","e":"ālāi"},{"b":"3.4","h":"5.19","c":"رَبِّكَ","d":"rbَkَِّ","e":"rabbika"},{"b":"4.3","h":"6.88","c":"تَتَمَارَى","d":"ttَmَāَràَٰ","e":"tatamārā"}],"a":{"g":"Then which of the favors of your Lord do you doubt?"}},"56":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.85","c":"هَذَا","d":"hdَٰhāَ","e":"hādhā"},{"b":"0.9","h":"2.34","c":"نَذِيرٌ","d":"ndَhyِrٌ","e":"nadhīrun"},{"b":"2.6","h":"4.54","c":"مِنَ","d":"mnَِّ","e":"mina"},{"b":"3.6","h":"5.1","c":"النُّذُرِ","d":"lٱndُّhrُِ","e":"l-nudhuri"},{"b":"4.7","h":"6.79","c":"الْأُولَى","d":"lٱʾْawُlàَٰٓ","e":"l-ūlā"}],"a":{"g":"This [Prophet] is a warner like the former warners."}},"57":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.65","c":"أَزِفَتِ","d":"ʾazَfِtَِ","e":"azifati"},{"b":"0.85","h":"2","c":"الْءَازِفَةُ","d":"lٱءْāَzfِẗَُ","e":"l-āzifatu"}],"a":{"g":"The Approaching Day has approached."}},"58":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.95","c":"لَيْسَ","d":"lyَsَْ","e":"laysa"},{"b":"0.69","h":"1.95","c":"لَهَا","d":"lhَāَ","e":"lahā"},{"b":"1.3","h":"3.06","c":"مِنْ","d":"mnِ","e":"min"},{"b":"2.6","h":"4.14","c":"دُونِ","d":"dwُnِ","e":"dūni"},{"b":"3.4","h":"5.28","c":"اللَّهِ","d":"lٱlhَِّ","e":"l-lahi"},{"b":"4.3","h":"6.67","c":"كَاشِفَةٌ","d":"kāَshfِẗٌَ","e":"kāshifatun"}],"a":{"g":"Of it, [from those] besides Allah, there is no remover."}},"59":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"1.05","c":"أَفَمِنْ","d":"ʾafَmَnِْ","e":"afamin"},{"b":"0.8","h":"2.18","c":"هَذَا","d":"hdَٰhāَ","e":"hādhā"},{"b":"1.5","h":"3.37","c":"الْحَدِيثِ","d":"lٱḥْdَyِthِ","e":"l-ḥadīthi"},{"b":"2.6","h":"5.07","c":"تَعْجَبُونَ","d":"tعَʿgْjbَwُnَ","e":"taʿjabūna"}],"a":{"g":"Then at this statement do you wonder?","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                وقال عز وجل: ﴿ أفمن هذا الحديث تعجبون وتضحكون ولا تبكون وأنتم سامدون ﴾ {} بل أقول كل ما ورد في فضل البكاء من خشية الله فهو إظهار لفضيلة الخشية فإن البكاء ثمرة الخشية فقد قال تعالى: ﴿ فليضحكوا قليلا وليبكوا كثيرا ﴾ {} وقال تعالى: ﴿ يبكون ويزيدهم خشوعا ﴾ {} وقال عز وجل: ﴿ أفمن هذا الحديث تعجبون وتضحكون ولا تبكون وأنتم سامدون ﴾ {}\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, do you then wonder at this discourse [hadith], and laugh and do not weep, while you amuse yourselves [samidun]?\n\nRather, I say: All that has come regarding the virtue of weeping from fear of Allah [khashya] is a manifestation of the virtue of fear [khashya], for weeping is the fruit of fear [khashya]. Indeed, He, the Exalted, has said: \"So let them laugh a little and weep much.\" And He, the Exalted, has said: \"They weep, and it increases them in humility [khushu'].\" And He, the Mighty and Majestic, has said: \"Indeed, do you then wonder at this discourse [hadith], and laugh and do not weep, while you amuse yourselves [samidun]?\"\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"60":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.9","c":"وَتَضْحَكُونَ","d":"wtَḍَḥْkَwُnَ","e":"wataḍḥakūna"},{"b":"1.6","h":"3.32","c":"وَلَا","d":"wlَāَ","e":"walā"},{"b":"2.2","h":"4.41","c":"تَبْكُونَ","d":"tbَkْwُnَ","e":"tabkūna"}],"a":{"g":"And you laugh and do not weep"}},"61":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.35","c":"وَأَنْتُمْ","d":"wʾَanَtmُْ","e":"wa-antum"},{"b":"2.0","h":"2.44","c":"سَامِدُونَ","d":"smَٰdِwُnَ","e":"sāmidūna"}],"a":{"g":"While you are proudly sporting?"}},"62":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.9","c":"فَاسْجُدُوا","d":"fsٱَgْjdُwُā۟","e":"fa-us'judū"},{"b":"1.1","h":"2.61","c":"لِلَّهِ","d":"llِhَِّ","e":"lillahi"},{"b":"2.4","h":"4.38","c":"وَاعْبُدُوا","d":"wعٱَʿbْdُwُā۟","e":"wa-uʿ'budū"}],"a":{"g":"So prostrate to Allah and worship [Him]."}}}